{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"e3c4494f-e5b3-491a-ac12-2762cfb40b51","content":"Neither — use `dotnet watch`. That's the command that enables hot reload. It monitors your files and automatically re-runs on changes.\n\nFor tests:\n```bash\ndotnet watch test\n```\n\nFor apps:\n```bash\ndotnet watch run\n```\n\n`dotnet test` and `dotnet run` execute once and exit — they don't watch for file changes. The `dotnet watch` wrapper is what provides the hot reload behavior.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"aa9de9cc-412d-4830-a8ac-d1f65e57c017","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about how to use hot reload with .NET testing. Let me look at the project files to understand what they're working with.","outputTokens":146,"requestId":"1BC2:315D54:661D9D:742220:6A03DCEF"},"id":"dac42437-cb91-4a0d-9fd3-b6e40eb88141","timestamp":"2026-05-13T02:07:48.792Z","parentId":"b45e9adc-d54a-4645-823a-3003e0d429e6"}
